==Useful Info==
'''Orcs''' are simple-minded creatures. Alone, they aren't much stronger than a [[goblin]] or [[kobold (monster)|kobold]]. However, orcs usually appear in packs. Worse yet, these packs often contain more dangerous orcs, including [[orc priest]]s and [[orc warrior|warriors]]. Orc packs are found throughout the Dungeon, the [[Orcish Mines]], and certain [[bailey]]s.

===Variant Orcs===
[[File:Deformed orc.png]]You can find '''deformed orcs''', '''febrile orcs''', and '''sickly orcs''' in some of the sealed chambers in [[Cigotuvi's Fleshworks]].

{{Flavour|This poor creature looks hideously deformed.}}

==Tips & Tricks==
*Orcs are often a sign that [[orc priest]]s, [[orc wizard|wizards]], and/or [[orc warrior|warriors]] are around. Try to lure packs to a hallway, staircase, or other choke point.

==History==
*In [[0.27]], the hidden weapon penalties for monsters were removed, so all monsters hit harder and faster with weapons. To compensate, orc's base damage was reduced from 5 to 2, though they always generate with a weapon.

